== Ubuntu server
## Login information
# user: myroot
# pass: testtest
- 'myroot' can become root through sudo
## System details
- no graphic card
- serial console configured for system and grub
- hostname configured according to VM_NAME from fast-vm
- system installed using minimal option with 'OpenSSH server' group enabled
- system would be running for the first time after installation
- disk drive connection - SCSI drive using virtio SCSI controller (supports TRIM)
## Drive layout
- 10 GB drive
  - default_size /boot
  - LVM name (uXXYYvg, for. example Ubuntu 14.04 will have VG name u1404vg)
    - 256MB swap_lv
    - 5GB root_lv
    - rest is free space on VG uXXYYvg

== Ubuntu Server LTS (manually installed)
## Login information
# user: root
# pass: testtest
(additionally user 'ubuntu' with password 'testtest' is present)
## System details
- no graphic card
- serial console configured for system and grub
- hostname configured according to VM_NAME from fast-vm
- typical server install with 'install OpenSSH server' option enabled
- system would be running for the first time after installation
- disk drive connection - SCSI drive using virtio SCSI controller (supports TRIM)
## Drive layout
- 6 GB drive
  - bios_grub partition (1MB)
  - /boot (512MB ext4)
  - LVM name (uXXYYvg, for. example Ubuntu 20.04 will have VG name u2004vg)
    - 5GB root_lv (ext4)
    - 256MB swap_lv
    - rest is free space on VG uXXYYvg
